                            <comment id="13968252" author="eirbjo" created="Mon, 14 Apr 2014 11:18:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reduced Maven project with test cases reproducing the issue &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13968261" author="eirbjo" created="Mon, 14 Apr 2014 11:34:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-4334&quot; title=&quot;Schema validation does not validate elements in soap header&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CXF-4334&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CXF-4334&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, Freeman Fang mentions that I could re-attach that test-case with &quot;Grant Apache License&quot; so that it could be included in the CXF code base.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t seem to find a switch like that in Jira now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/INFRA-4708&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/INFRA-4708&lt;/a&gt; indicates that I should follow &quot;Manage attachments&quot;, but I can&apos;t seem to find anything related to license grants there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For stopping regressions and having a place to add more test cases related to validation, I&apos;d like to get both that test case and the test case attached to this issue uploaded with any necessary grants applied.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13968287" author="eirbjo" created="Mon, 14 Apr 2014 12:08:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m assuming this issue is releated to the switch to Woodstox in 2.7.7?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13968583" author="dkulp" created="Mon, 14 Apr 2014 17:55:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Quick note to self:  CXF isn&apos;t detecting a &quot;return&quot; of a fault from a Provider (as apposed to a &quot;thrown&quot; fault) and is thus not putting it on the fault out chain and thus not setting the response code to 500.  Both PAYLOAD and MESSAGE is affected by this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
